VJust for KidsMoser Baer India Ltd.Entertainment VCDPrice (Rs. 49)Conceived by V.Murali Raman and produced by Jaya TV, Moser Baer  has brought out this VCD that contains interesting shorts meant for kids, mainly pre-schoolers and those in kindergarten.  This one-hour VCD is spread over five segments each running up to 20 minutes.Moser Baer &#8212; DVDProducer: Ramaas CompanyPrice: Rs.69&#8216;For the first time Audio Tracks + Video,&#8217; says the jacket of the DVD titled &#8216;Kavidhaiyae Paadalaaga &#8230;&#8217; Part 2. The 10 songs penned by Vairamuthu have been set to music by Iniyavan and sung by a host of popular singers.Moser BaerT.H.Vikku Vinayakaram and teamFusion music VCDPrice: Rs. 49An amalgam of vocal and instrumental music is rendered in the form of fusion by a team of artists led by ghatam maestro Vikku Vinayakaram. He is joined by N.Ramakrishnan (mridangam), V.Selva Ganesh (ganjira), V.Umashankar and D.V.Venkata Subramaniam (ghatam), N.Rajaraman (gethu vadhyam), A.Ganesan (morsing) and Mahesh Vinayakram (vocal). Enjoy this rhythm experience in nine segments, viz., Shiva Thandav, Aadityahridayam, 160 degrees, Chathur ghatam, Flying leaf, Rhy &#8216;N&#8217; 9, voice of rhythm, sapthaakshara and folk journey.Sanskriti SeriesSwathi Soft SolutionsClassical &#8211; DVD (English)Price: Rs. 150This 85-minute visual treat presents the bhakti-laden music of Tanjore S.Kalyanaraman. Also featured is the analysis of various aspects of the music of SKR, as he is fondly called, by legends, maestros, patrons and budding musicians and also his principal disciples.Script &amp; direction: S.B.Kanthan, editing: V.Krishan Kumar, Created by Brinda Venkataramanan, Bhushany Kalyanaraman, voice-over: S.Muralidhar.Visalakshi NityanandCarnatic Vocal &#8211; CDPrice: Rs.150This four-in-one CD pack comprises the renditions of Visalakshi Nityanand.The recital includes Oothukadu compositions, Dikshitar kritis and an RTP in Nattakurinji.
